@lilars26:It means after 48 hrs 20-40 stops seeding the torrent!

@lilars: I could try. "TimeToLive 48h" is common practice on good private tracker sites and tells for how long torrent would be seeded from main seeding server. After "expiration" time some sites automatically delete such tagged torrents - knowing that there is no point in longer seeding.

That's true here too, If anyone misses some show for TWO days, this is not a right place to look for.

Anyway, downloader still have a chance here at Sunday's Weekly TV packs. Last one was kept active for four days - and if anyone haven't downloaded in six frikkin days - I humbly suggest to go someplace else.
